{"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (14 min)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10681","type":"reference"}},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC20","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Swan’s Quest, Chapter 1: Voices in the dark"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift Playgrounds presents “Swan’s Quest,” an interactive adventure in four chapters for all ages. In this chapter, our Hero must navigate a dark cave — and the only way to light the torches is to make them accessible."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10681-swans-quest-chapter-1-voices-in-the-dark"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10681-Swans-Quest-Chapter-1-Voices-in-the-dark"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swan’s Quest is a series of challenges where each chapter has a specific programming challenge for you that will build on the prior chapters."}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Download the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".playgroundbook"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/sample-code\/swift\/swans-quest\/voices-in-the-dark.zip","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"VoiceOver","anchor":"VoiceOver","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To complete the first challenge, you’re going to use VoiceOver.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"What is VoiceOver?","anchor":"What-is-VoiceOver","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"VoiceOver is Apple’s screen reader","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"VoiceOver provides information about text, controls, and other elements as you move through an app’s interface using text-to-speech, Braille, or a combination of the two."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this chapter, you’re gonna write code using VoiceOver.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Getting Started","anchor":"Getting-Started","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Toggling VoiceOver","anchor":"Toggling-VoiceOver","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"text":"iOS\/iPadOS","anchor":"iOSiPadOS","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make it easy for us to toggle VoiceOver: go to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Settings > Accessibility > Accessibility Shortcut"},{"type":"text","text":" and choose VoiceOver."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will enable you to toggle VoiceOver by pressing three times the home button or the side button (depending on your iPhone form factor).","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can also ask Siri to turn on\/off VoiceOver"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"text":"macOS","anchor":"macOS","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"code":"⌘ + F5","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or triple-click the TouchID button to activate VoiceOver."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can move the VoiceOver cursor through the screen by pressing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"⌃ + ⌥"},{"type":"text","text":" plus either the Left or Right Arrow keys."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can navigate up and down by using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"⌃ + ⌥"},{"text":" plus the Up or Down Arrow keys.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To enter a group of controls or elements such as the Source Code Editor in Playgrounds, press "},{"code":"⌃ + ⌥ + ⇧","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" plus the Down Arrow to do what it’s called "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"interacting"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To stop interacting, to get out of a group of controls, press "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"⌃ + ⌥ + ⇧"},{"type":"text","text":" plus the Up Arrow key."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"⌃ + ⌥","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" plus the Space Bar to activate a control.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Getting Familiar with Voice Over","anchor":"Getting-Familiar-with-Voice-Over","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once activated, a black rectangle around the selected control will appear, this is called the VoiceOver cursor, and it confirms visually which item has VoiceOver’s focus."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can flick left or right with one finger to move the cursor over different elements on the screen."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can drag your finger around the screen to move the cursor over elements more quickly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To leave an app either:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"press the Home button"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slide one finger up from the bottom edge of the screen until you hear the first sound. If you pause there, VoiceOver will say, “Lift for Home.”. Lift for Home."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"SPCAccessibility","anchor":"SPCAccessibility","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For this first challenge, a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SPCAccessibility"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PlaygroundModule"},{"type":"text","text":" has been built, this module is part of the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/sample-code\/swift\/swans-quest\/quest-create.zip"},{"type":"text","text":" Playground Book."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SPCAccessibility"},{"text":" has four on-screen elements that form its foundation:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Graphic","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Button"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Sprite","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Label"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of them inherit from "},{"code":"BaseGraphic","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which contains properties for accessibility support."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An example of accessibility property is ","type":"text"},{"code":"AccessibilityHints","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property: setting this property indicates that this screen element should be read by VoiceOver, and makes it visible to other assistive services.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To support VoiceOver, these are the values you need to supply:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeAccessibilityElement"},{"type":"text","text":" tells VoiceOver it should stop the cursor on this item."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"accessibilityLabel"},{"type":"text","text":" is what VoiceOver reads as it stops on the item."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"To pass the first challenge..","anchor":"To-pass-the-first-challenge","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"..you will need to make the screen elements accessible."}]},{"text":"Solution","anchor":"Solution","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"code":["cave.torch1.accessibilityHints?.accessibilityLabel = \"First torch\"","cave.torch2.accessibilityHints?.accessibilityLabel = \"Second torch\"","cave.torch3.accessibilityHints?.accessibilityLabel = \"Third torch\"","cave.torch4.accessibilityHints?.accessibilityLabel = \"Fourth torch\"","cave.torch5.accessibilityHints?.accessibilityLabel = \"Fifth torch\"","cave.torch6.accessibilityHints?.accessibilityLabel = \"Sixth torch\""],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Written By","anchor":"Written-By","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"numberOfColumns":5,"columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Federico Zanetello","anchor":"Federico-Zanetello"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","isActive":true}]}],"size":4}],"type":"row"},